news.title: Mumbai: BMC stays its proposal to hike rent of civic-owned properties
news.para: There are close to 3,500 BMC owned properties in the city. The last hike was implemented back in the year 2014 following which, in 2021, the BMC had floated a proposal of increasing the rates to Rs 3 per square feet.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body chief raps officials over illegal buildings, pending NOCs
news.para: The municipal town planner has been told to review recovery status daily with assistant town planners and to take strict action against illegal structures.

news.title: Goa-SEIAA fines builder Rs 50 lakh for starting project without EC
news.para: The authority has laid down the condition that the project proponent shall not make any change in the surface layout plan or civil plan submitted to Goa-SEIAA without its prior permission.

news.title: Sebi fines 21 entities for manipulating share price of Sunstar Realty Development
news.para: Sebi conducted an investigation in the scrip of Sunstar Realty Development Ltd (SRDL) during June 2015 to March 2016 to ascertain whether there were any violations of the PFUTP (Prohibition of Fraudulent and Unfair Trade Practices) rules.

news.title: No irregularities in SBUT redevelopment: Brihanmumbai civic body panel
news.para: The committee was set up by Chahal on October 17 at the behest of the state urban development department, two months after the annoucement of an inquiry.

news.title: Revenue authorities cite hurdles to execute MahaRERA orders
news.para: With nearly 751 recovery warrant orders to be executed, the authorities are facing issues with carrying out the orders and ensuring that homebuyers receive their invested money back.

news.title: NBCC Green View buyers write to housing minister, seek rent relief extension
news.para: By July, NBCC had put forward its first compensation package to the homebuyers, saying that it will refund their original purchase amounts - in the range of Rs 65 lakh to Rs 1.5 crore - along with the sum spent on registry.

news.title: Gurugram: Three builders fail to clear audit dues, may face action
news.para: "These three developers were directed to deposit the structural audit fees latest by Monday evening. However, none of them has complied with the directions," Gurugram's deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav said on Tuesday.

news.title: ICICI Bank and Indian Bank hike benchmark lending rates
news.para: ​Private sector lender ICICI Bank increased the Marginal Cost of Funds based Lending Rates (MCLR) across tenure by 20 basis points effective November 1.

news.title: Macrotech Developers posts Rs 933 crore net loss in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 1,761.23 crore in Q2 FY23, a drop of 17.61 per cent from Rs 2,137.76 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: CIFI Holdings' suspended debt repayments add to China's property woes
news.para: CIFI said in a filing it has engaged Haitong International Securities Company Limited as financial advisor and Linklaters as legal adviser to facilitate a restructuring of its $6.85 billion offshore debt, as it is likely to come under continued pressure to generate sufficient cash for repayments.

news.title: IWG expects annual profit at lower end of market estimates
news.para: The group said it remains "cautiously optimistic" about the full year, as it forecast adjusted core profit to come in the lower end of the range of market expectations of 304 million pounds to 380 million pounds ($350.69 million to $438.37 million).

news.title: China: Greenland Holdings seeks offshore bond payment extension
news.para: State-backed Greenland joins a string of Chinese developers that have delayed or defaulted on offshore debt obligations since the second half of last year due to a stifling cash squeeze triggered partly by a regulatory crackdown.

news.title: China property slump persists in October with falling prices, sales as covid bites
news.para: China's property sector, once a pillar of growth, has slowed sharply in the past year as a result of a government clampdown on excessive borrowing by developers, and a COVID-19-induced economic slump.

news.title: Dehradun civic body to charge user fees for multi-storeyed apartments
news.para: User fees have been increased up to five times as a shopkeeper has to pay Rs 100 per month for running a shop in residential areas, instead of present Rs 20.
